{
  "texts": [
    "The GPT architecture uses more than one block of attention mechanism per decoder layer.",
    "GPT-3 uses h = 96 attention heads (Brown et al. 2020).",
    "Intuition: Each head of an attention block processes all the input but learns to focus on various aspects of the input token sequence when computing co-relevance scores.",
    "The SoftMax function distributes the co-relevance scores differently, depending on the levels of dot product mix that each attention head computes and on how the FFNN in the previous layer transformed the previous contextualized vectors.",
    "With multiple attention heads learning different focus areas, the final concatenation of the attention vectors will have a richer mix of co-relevance from multiple parts of the input sequence."
  ]
}